The paper discusses the development of a machine learning model (LSTM) for predicting traffic flow parameters using connected vehicle data. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a Kalman filter-based noise reduction model, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of statistical analysis to evaluate the performance of the model, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
